Help on skill:     Kiru
Usage duration:    2 rounds
Fatigue:           minimal
Skill type:        attack
Affecting stat(s): strength, dexterity, kiru, zhinakoku, hiding, weapon mastery
                   and weapon stats

Kiru is a blade fighting technique in which the Samurai Warrior invests
all his physical strength and dexterity to perform a stunning attack on
his enemy. The bladed attacks of 'Kiru' were originally designed to
inflict terror and pain to the Samurai's opponent. However, when
employed by one of the most legendary of the Samurais, the sudden death
of the Samurai's opponent also becomes a very real possibility.

The Samurai's inner spirit affects his ability to follow-up his initial
kiru attack with secondary and tertiary attack maneuvers.

When wielding the Tebukuro-ken with inner spirit active, a successful
kiru may channel battle spirit into regenerative energy, mending wounds
through meridian flow. This requires knowledge of the shizen spell.

Should the stunning strike fail against a resilient opponent, advanced
tessenjutsu mastery may awaken reflexively, allowing the warrior's body
to flow like wind through leaves, achieving a state of formless defense.

The Samurai Artists are able to perform the stronger and more exhaustive
version of the Kiru attack developed by the legendary Samurai Artist,
Shogun Naganoro.

Syntax: use kiru at <target> <strong>.
