Help on skill: Legendary conjury.
Usage duration: automatic.
Skill type: special.
Affecting stat(s): skill perfect, intelligence and dexterity.
The Magus Artiste are oft-times derided by the so-called professional
magic-users for their very narrow focus and their tendency to just "wing it"
when it comes to magic. There is no doubt however that a truly talented
Magus Artiste is able to perform incredible feats when it comes to wielding
projectile magics. Even if they themselves do not know how exactly it all
works.
A Magus Artiste performing 'legendary conjury' essentially compresses
a magical projectile by channeling a great amount of energy into and around
it. This will make the conjuration of the projectile take a little more time but
will make it more stable and easier to control, allowing the Artiste to aim
it with incredible accuracy. Depending on the Artiste's proficiency and natural
hand-eye coordination, a spell conjured in this manner can cause severe,
critical injuries--potentially causing havoc only dreamed of by the traditional
spellcasters. Such manipulation will however make the projectile less
devastating should the Artiste's aim be off.
Possessing knowledge of the opponent's anatomy will surely aid in aiming
the projectile into the most vital parts. A keen mind that is always on the
lookout for weaknesses in an opponent's defenses has also been found to
make a difference.
While the casting of projectile magics comes naturally to the Magus Artiste,
most have stated that it is even easier while performing the 'legendary conjury'.
