Help on skill: Mystifying flourish.
Usage duration: automatic.
Skill type: special.
Affecting stat(s): skill percent, dexterity and charisma.
The Magus Artiste have a lot in common with jesters and jugglers, more
so than they have with mages for example. There is a decidedly artistic
element present in all the magics of the Artiste, and for some reason it
also appears to be of great benefit.
When performing 'mystifying flourish' the Magus Artiste adds fancy gestures
and steps, even dance-like routines, to his spellcasting. Either this
prancing about truly does make the spells stronger or the on-lookers are
just so bewildered by it, that they are caught completely unawares by the
destructive projectiles. Either way, the agility and the charisma of the
Magus Artiste will now play a greater role in the effectiveness of the spells.
While a spell magnified in this manner does not drain additional magical
energy, the flourishing is slightly fatiguing in the long run. In most
cases the magical drain have actually been found to be lessened, suggesting
that there actually might be something real in these strange methods--
some wonder that essentially allows a Magus Artiste to convert physical energy,
stamina, into magical energy to fuel their spells.
A Magus Artiste who is especially talented and charismatic is often
able to hide the initiated spellcasting, though not by concealing it like
the psionicists do but rather disguising it with artistic embellishments
into something entirely harmless.
