The Magus Artiste are known first and foremost for their incredible
accuracy and agility with projectile spells. But anyone who is expecting
an Artiste to always take their time and carefully aim each shot, is likely
to be unpleasantly surprised. When forgoing most of the time-consuming aiming
an Artiste is able to focus all their considerable talents into conjuring the
magics as quickly as possible, thus creating an overwhelming barrage of
projectiles. Needless to say, the accuracy of each shot is greatly reduced.
The energy of the projectiles is also lessened as the Artiste does not spend
as much time channeling the magic.
