information about the enemy can be gathered. Haphazardly throwing
ones offensive abilities at a target is thus pointless, and something
more calculated is required to buy sufficient time in the heat of the
battle. In order to increase their own survivability and to reduce
the combat effectiveness of an adversary, the invokers of the Golden
Company have devised the technique of the Sundering Star. By enchanting
their shield with the sidereal energies and striking the enemy with it
can they do just that.
The efficiency of this skill is largely determined by the amount of
defensive Golden Arts the invoker is currently performing as well as
the users proximity to the target.
If used with an armament of sufficient elemental potency, this ability
often causes the target to become susceptible to followup attacks.
This attack can only be executed while wielding a sword and a shield.
