A good healer knows exactly how to manipulate body energies and raw magic
into tangiable, life giving form, but the best healers know how to mold
this ever-present flow of life into form with such speed that can only come
from knowing the fabric of the heart of the world itself. Diligent study of
the natural flow of life around us grants speed to the caster of true heal
spells which, while difficult to truly master, can sometimes provide that
added deftness to a heal which could make all the difference between life
and death.
---------------------------------------------------
Help on skill:  Enhanced evasion
Usage duration: automatic
Skill type:     special

The nimbleness of the goblins is unlike the graceful agility of the elves,
or the predatory litheness of the catfolk. It is best described as a
talent for weaseling in and out of things, a physical and metaphysical
slipperiness that makes goblins hard to pin down in all of their affairs.
Enhanced evasion harnesses this instinctive cunning into a more refined
set of techniques designed for combat. Training in enhanced evasion
significantly improves the rate at which goblins dodge, reduces penalties
caused by carried weight, and reduces fatigue caused by dodging.
---------------------------------------------------
Help on skill:  Hoodwink
Usage duration: automatic
Skill type:     special

Goblins are among the world's best hagglers, but they have no rivals in the
world of confidence tricks -- which they view almost as a form of sport.
The best tricks prey on the avarice of others, by making the mark think he
is taking advantage of the confidence artist, when the reverse is actually
true. Goblins have a vast repertoire of such techniques, which they deploy
almost without thinking, turning every interaction into a game of
oneupsmanship and tactical advantage. 'Hoodwinking' is what goblins call
this, and it comes in especially handy during business dealings.
A goblin practiced in this technique will occasionally be able to sell
items at inflated prices far exceeding their ordinary sale value,
through the use of confidence tricks and other ruses.
---------------------------------------------------
Help on skill:  Purse-cutting
Usage duration: automatic
Skill type:     special

The instinctive opportunism of goblins is so strong, so pervasive, that
it could be called compulsive. Just as water seeks out cracks in stone,
the goblin mind constantly searches for openings that it can exploit,
at every moment, in every interaction.

The thrusting maneuver taught by the thieves' guild brings the user within
close range of the victim, where he must rely on deft footwork and
misdirection to land a quick strike on his mark. Goblins regard all
this work as a missed opportunity - to come so close to the valuables of
one's target, only to leave them intact and in place. The technique
of purse-cutting allows a skilled goblin to make more out of thrusting,
with blows aimed to cut purse strings and pilfer extra coins from the victim.
These thrusts may also expose weaknesses that increase damage done by later
attacks.
---------------------------------------------------
Help on skill:  Facilitating payments
Usage duration: automatic
Skill type:     special

The couther races of the world cherish such virtues as love, valor,
honesty, loyalty and sacrifice. But the shrewd and practical goblins
have little use for these frail sentiments. They know but one thing
makes the world go 'round: money. Lots and lots of money.

It is customary in certain offices and certain quarters to furnish
government officials with a token of one's appreciation. Such 'tips'
may accelerate the performance of official functions, or encourage
decisions in the donor's favor. Goblins understand that other races
frown upon such practices, but they consider this self-righteousness
to be hopelessly naive. Money turns the wheels of commerce, and
facilitating payments are nothing more than a necessary cost of doing
business. These bribes are especially effective at influencing the
outcomes of games of chance, such as lotteries, that leave room for
human influence and intervention.  This skill teaches accepted methods
of government bribery, and proficiency reduces the amounts necessary
to bribe various officials.
---------------------------------------------------
Help on skill:  Metachrosis
Usage duration: automatic
Skill type:     special

Of all the greenskin races, goblins best live up to the name. All but
a rare few have green-pigmented features, and this telltale skin,
together with their short stature and long, crooked noses, are
considered by many to be the race's distinguishing features.

Little do these outsiders know, for the pigment in a goblin's skin
is no ordinary substance. It changes color, often quite dramatically,
in response to danger, injury, and other external stimuli. Disciplined
goblins can learn to exert control over these involuntary responses,
harnessing their chameleonic tendencies to blend at will into their
surroundings. Training in this skill, called metachrosis, allows
goblins to hide more quickly and expertly, and to stay hidden when moving.
---------------------------------------------------
Help on skill:  Sabotage
Usage duration: automatic
Skill type:     special

Goblins have survived for centuries in the company of savages, shunned
by the finer races, dwarved and bullied by their more feral kin.
Cunning, subterfuge and sabotage have been the key to the goblins'
survival. What they lack in might and mystical ability, they make up for
with amorality and a shrewd lack of scruples. In warfare, a goblin's goal
is simple: survive by any means necessary. Goblins do not believe in such
a thing as 'honorable' combat. Violence is unavoidably vicious, and
those who aim to make it noble are either deluded or lying. Only fools
would handicap themselves by using less than all available tools at their
disposal. Goblins do not suffer fools gladly.

It should come as no surprise, given their philosophical leanings, that
goblins have become masters of poisons and other tools of 'foul' play. These
methods have been the key to the species' survival from its beginnings.
The art of sabotage improves the effectiveness of poisons mixed by a goblin,
and enhances his natural affinity with poisons, increasing damage done by
all poison attacks.
---------------------------------------------------
Help on skill:  Cabinetry
Usage duration: automatic
Skill type:     special

Goblins are crafty, but they are not apt to be craftsmen, preferring to
leave nuanced artisanry to the finer races. Even so, goblins have an
abiding interest in cabinets, drawers, trunks, chests, and just about
any object that can be used to store valuables -- from a technical, if
not an aesthetic standpoint. The study of cabinetry familiarizes goblins
with the carpentry methods involved in making containers, which comes in
handy when inspecting the panels and joints of chests for hidden
compartments. Cabinetry experts may thus discover special treasure within
ordinary, everyday containers.
---------------------------------------------------

Help on skill:     Quantum sleight
Usage duration:    random
Fatigue:           minimal
Skill type:        attack
Affecting stat(s): charisma and dexterity

Goblins are not wordsmiths, but they have a penchant for borrowing memorable,
usually cryptic, turns of phrase. One of their favorite proverbs holds: 'The
distinction between the past, present and future is a stubbornly
persistent illusion.' Whatever this once meant, goblins interpret it
in only one way: time, if illusory, is ripe for exploitation.

And so came about the ruse of the 'quantum sleight,' a peculiar form of illusion
that tricks the victim into believing he is frozen in time. Time, of course,
does not actually stop -- the illusionist and third parties may continue to
move and act normally while the illusion is in effect. The victim, however,
fixates on a specific moment in the past and stays in that moment until the
sleight wears off.  The victim will be unable to move or attack, and any skills
or spells he was using will be paused, then resumed when the illusion subsides.

This trick can only be performed with some kind of magical timepiece, which
serves to focus the user's temporal magic, and to hypnotize the victim, making
him susceptible to suggestion. The skill places some strain on the timepiece,
which will need time to recover before this skill can be used again. The
quality of the illusion depends on the quality of the timepiece, along with
the user's charisma, mastery of illusion, and training in both quantum sleight
and spacial manipulation. Dexterity speeds up the performance.
---------------------------------------------------

Help on skill:  Creative accounting
Usage duration: automatic
Skill type:     special

Banking regulations prevent certain entrepreneurial spirits from storing
their ill-gotten gains in traditional financial institutions. But a shrewd
businessperson can overcome this limitation by concealing the source of
money through clever bookkeeping. Practitioners of creative accounting
learn to prepare financial statements so dense, circular and unintelligible
that even banking professionals will be deceived. Any amount of training
in this skill will permit the user to store money in the banks of the land,
albeit at an increased tax rate. Additional training reduces the rate of
taxation, while high levels of proficiency enable the user to evade taxes
almost completely.
