Throw aside every lesson about protection. Abandon guard. Overextend.
Commit everything, body, weapon, fury itself, into one devastating strike
delivered with such overwhelming force that the enemy's defense becomes
meaningless. Let them see the opening you create. Let them understand what's
coming. It changes nothing.

This is not technique or strategy. This is the moment when you decide that
killing your enemy matters more than your own safety, and you make that
decision with steel and fury. Either they fall or you do.

